{"title_page": "Linda Nedbalov\u00e1", "text_new": "{{short description|Czech Antarctic researcher, phycologist}}\n{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Linda Nedbalov\u00e1\n| image = Sampling James Ross.jpg\n| caption = Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 at [[James Ross Island]]\n| birth_name        =1976 \n| death_date        = \n| nationality       = [[Czech Republic]]\n| fields = [[Cryosphere]] ecology\n| workplaces        = [[Charles University]], Prague\n| alma_mater        = [[Charles University]], Prague.\n| awards            = [[Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic]] Award\n| website           = {{url|http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova}}\n}}\n\n'''Linda Nedbalov\u00e1''' is a Czech [[Antarctic]] researcher, best known for her work on [[snow algae]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/biologie/ekologie/aktuality/Nedbalova_AVCR|title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 z\u00edskala presti\u017en\u00ed Cenu Akademie v\u011bd \u010cR. Gratulujeme!|website=www.natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 wins the prestigious Award of the Academy of Sciences. Congratulations!|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nNedbalov\u00e1 was born in 1976 in [[Prague]] (Czech Republic). She received her MSc. degree in biology in 2000 at the Faculty of Science, [[Charles University in Prague|Charles University]] in Prague. She then received a Ph.D. at the same faculty in 2007. The title of her thesis was '''Phytoplankton in acidified lakes: structure, function and response to ecosystem recovery''<nowiki/>'.\n\n==Career and impact==\nNedbalov\u00e1 began her working career as a researcher both at the Institute of Botany of the Czech Academy of Sciences in T\u0159ebo\u0148 and at the Department of Ecology, Charles University in Prague, where she is now assistant professor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/biology/ecology/people/staff|title=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdeck\u00e1 fakulta|website=www.natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Staff|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> Nedbalov\u00e1 has been involved in polar research since 2008, when she was invited to participate on the expedition to the newly opened [[Johann Gregor Mendel Czech Antarctic Station]] on [[James Ross Island]] (NE Antarctic Peninsula).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://polar.sci.muni.cz/en/station-jgm|title=Station J.G.M. - Polar research at Masaryk University|website=polar.sci.muni.cz|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> In 2011, she was awarded a prestigious award of the [[Czech Academy of Sciences|Czech Academy of Science]] for Young scientists for her work on [[Watermelon snow|snow algae]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nDuring two consecutive expeditions to Antarctica, she performed (together with Josef Elster) a pioneering [[Limnology|limnological survey]] of the [[Ulu Peninsula]] and Clearwater [[Mesa]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nedbalov\u00e1|first=Linda|last2=N\u00fdvlt|first2=Daniel|last3=Kop\u00e1\u010dek|first3=Ji\u0159\u00ed|last4=\u0160obr|first4=Miroslav|last5=Elster|first5=Josef|date=2013-06-01|title=Freshwater lakes of Ulu Peninsula, James Ross Island, north-east Antarctic Peninsula: origin, geomorphology and physical and chemical limnology|journal=Antarctic Science|volume=25|issue=3|pages=358\u2013372|doi=10.1017/S0954102012000934|issn=1365-2079|bibcode=2013AntSc..25..358N}}</ref> Apart from the first characteristics of the lake district, this research yielded (in collaboration with specialists as Bart van de Vijver or Ji\u0159\u00ed Kom\u00e1rek) important results in taxonomy, ecology, ecophysiology and biogeography of Antarctic cyanobacteria, diatoms and green algae. Recently, she became a member of the Cryosphere Ecology Group formed at the Charles University in Prague.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova/|title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1|website=www.cryoeco.eu|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to her academic research publications, she has also written chapters in monographs,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sci.muni.cz/CPR/Prosek-Book_Preview.pdf|title=Forthcoming monography in Czech|last=|first=|date=|website=sci.muni.cz|publisher=Masaryk University|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/fakulta/aktuality/antarktida-2013-prvni-puvodni-ceska-monografie|title=Antarktida \u2013 prvn\u00ed p\u016fvodn\u00ed \u010desk\u00e1 monografie|last=|first=|date=|website=natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Antarctica - the first original Czech monograph|access-date=}}</ref> popular science articles,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ziva.avcr.cz/2007-3/kdyz-snih-zcervena-aneb-co-ne-vime-o-sneznych-rasach.html|title=Kdy\u017e sn\u00edh z\u010derven\u00e1, aneb co (ne)v\u00edme o sn\u011b\u017en\u00fdch \u0159as\u00e1ch|date=2016|website=ziva.avcr.cz|publisher=\u017diva|trans-title=When snow turns red, or what (not) know about Snow Algae|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prirodovedci.cz/storage/files/160/prirodovedci-04-2014.pdf|title=\u017divot v extr\u00e9mech|last=|first=|date=2014|website=prirodovedci.cz|publisher=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdci|trans-title=Life in the extremes|access-date=}}</ref> reports from Antarctic expeditions,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/odlet-znacne-znesnadnilo-pocasi/296323|title=Odlet zna\u010dn\u011b znesnadnilo po\u010das\u00ed|date=2008|website=magazin.ceskenoviny.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny|trans-title=Departure made difficult due to forecast|access-date=2016-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826121145/http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/odlet-znacne-znesnadnilo-pocasi/296323|archive-date=2016-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/zprava-c-3-z-ostrova-jamese-rosse-vedecka-prace-se-rozbehla/354292|title=Zpr\u00e1va \u010d. 3 z ostrova Jamese Rosse: V\u011bdeck\u00e1 pr\u00e1ce se rozb\u011bhla|date=2009|website=magazin.ceskenoviny.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny|trans-title=Report no. 3 of the James Ross Island: Scientific work is started|access-date=2016-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826115259/http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/zprava-c-3-z-ostrova-jamese-rosse-vedecka-prace-se-rozbehla/354292|archive-date=2016-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/leonardo/veda/_zprava/dalsi-clenove-antarkticke-expedice-jsou-na-miste--542596|title=Dal\u0161\u00ed \u010dlenov\u00e9 antarktick\u00e9 expedice jsou na m\u00edst\u011b|date=2009|website=rozhlas.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00fd rozhlas|trans-title=Other members of the Antarctic expedition are in place|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> and lake ecosystems at James Ross Island.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prirodovedci.cz/storage/files/184/prirodovedci-03-2015-nahled-01.pdf|title=Antarktida|last=|first=|date=2015|website=prirodovedci.cz|publisher=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdci|trans-title=Antarctica|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://casopis.vesmir.cz/clanek/jezera-ostrova-jamese-rosse|title=Jezera ostrova Jamese Rosse|date=2012|website=casopis.vesmir.cz|publisher=Vesmir|trans-title=Lake James Ross Island|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abicko.avcr.cz/2013/07/06/antarktida.html|title=\u010cesk\u00e1 stopa v Antarktid\u011b|last=|first=|date=2013|website=abicko.avcr.cz|publisher=Academic bulletin|trans-title=Czech footprint in Antarctica|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honours==\nNedbalov\u00e1 was awarded the [[Czech Academy of Sciences|Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic]] Award to Young Researchers for Outstanding Achievements in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.avcr.cz/en/about-us/awards/prizes-of-the-cas/|title=Prizes of the CAS|website=www.avcr.cz|publisher=Akademie v\u011bd \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova/ Linda Nedbalova's webpage]\n* {{google scholar id|L1CmfTAAAAAJ}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nedbalova, Linda}}\n\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century biologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Czech biologists]]\n[[Category:Czech women biologists]]\n[[Category:Czech Antarctic scientists]]\n[[Category:Women Antarctic scientists]]\n[[Category:Phycologists]]\n[[Category:Women phycologists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Czech Antarctic researcher, phycologist}}\n{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Linda Nedbalov\u00e1\n| image = Sampling James Ross.jpg\n| caption = Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 at [[James Ross Island]]\n| birth_name        =1976 \n| death_date        = \n| nationality       = [[Czech Republic]]\n| fields = [[Cryosphere]] ecology\n| workplaces        = [[Charles University]], Prague\n| alma_mater        = [[Charles University]], Prague.\n| awards            = [[Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic]] Award\n| website           = {{url|http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova}}\n}}\n\n'''Linda Nedbalov\u00e1''' is a Czech [[Antarctic]] researcher, best known for her work on [[snow algae]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/biologie/ekologie/aktuality/Nedbalova_AVCR|title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 z\u00edskala presti\u017en\u00ed Cenu Akademie v\u011bd \u010cR. Gratulujeme!|website=www.natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1 wins the prestigious Award of the Academy of Sciences. Congratulations!|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nNedbalov\u00e1 was born in 1976 in [[Prague]] (Czech Republic). She received her MSc. degree in biology in 2000 at the Faculty of Science, [[Charles University in Prague|Charles University]] in Prague. She then received a Ph.D. at the same faculty in 2007. The title of her thesis was '''Phytoplankton in acidified lakes: structure, function and response to ecosystem recovery''<nowiki/>'.\n\n==Career and impact==\nNedbalov\u00e1 began her working career as a researcher both at the Institute of Botany of the Czech Academy of Sciences in T\u0159ebo\u0148 and at the Department of Ecology, Charles University in Prague, where she is now assistant professor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/biology/ecology/people/staff|title=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdeck\u00e1 fakulta|website=www.natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Staff|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> Nedbalov\u00e1 has been involved in polar research since 2008, when she was invited to participate on the expedition to the newly opened [[Johann Gregor Mendel Czech Antarctic Station]] on [[James Ross Island]] (NE Antarctic Peninsula).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://polar.sci.muni.cz/en/station-jgm|title=Station J.G.M. - Polar research at Masaryk University|website=polar.sci.muni.cz|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> In 2011, she was awarded a prestigious award of the [[Czech Academy of Sciences|Czech Academy of Science]] for Young scientists for her work on [[Watermelon snow|snow algae]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nDuring two consecutive expeditions to Antarctica, she performed (together with Josef Elster) a pioneering [[Limnology|limnological survey]] of the [[Ulu Peninsula]] and Clearwater [[Mesa]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nedbalov\u00e1|first=Linda|last2=N\u00fdvlt|first2=Daniel|last3=Kop\u00e1\u010dek|first3=Ji\u0159\u00ed|last4=\u0160obr|first4=Miroslav|last5=Elster|first5=Josef|date=2013-06-01|title=Freshwater lakes of Ulu Peninsula, James Ross Island, north-east Antarctic Peninsula: origin, geomorphology and physical and chemical limnology|journal=Antarctic Science|volume=25|issue=3|pages=358\u2013372|doi=10.1017/S0954102012000934|issn=1365-2079|bibcode=2013AntSc..25..358N}}</ref> Apart from the first characteristics of the lake district, this research yielded (in collaboration with specialists as Bart van de Vijver or Ji\u0159\u00ed Kom\u00e1rek) important results in taxonomy, ecology, ecophysiology and biogeography of Antarctic cyanobacteria, diatoms and green algae. Recently, she became a member of the Cryosphere Ecology Group formed at the Charles University in Prague.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova/|title=Linda Nedbalov\u00e1|website=www.cryoeco.eu|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to her academic research publications, she has also written chapters in monographs,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sci.muni.cz/CPR/Prosek-Book_Preview.pdf|title=Forthcoming monography in Czech|last=|first=|date=|website=sci.muni.cz|publisher=Masaryk University|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.natur.cuni.cz/fakulta/aktuality/antarktida-2013-prvni-puvodni-ceska-monografie|title=Antarktida \u2013 prvn\u00ed p\u016fvodn\u00ed \u010desk\u00e1 monografie|last=|first=|date=|website=natur.cuni.cz|publisher=Charles University|trans-title=Antarctica - the first original Czech monograph|access-date=}}</ref> popular science articles,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ziva.avcr.cz/2007-3/kdyz-snih-zcervena-aneb-co-ne-vime-o-sneznych-rasach.html|title=Kdy\u017e sn\u00edh z\u010derven\u00e1, aneb co (ne)v\u00edme o sn\u011b\u017en\u00fdch \u0159as\u00e1ch|date=2016|website=ziva.avcr.cz|publisher=\u017diva|trans-title=When snow turns red, or what (not) know about Snow Algae|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prirodovedci.cz/storage/files/160/prirodovedci-04-2014.pdf|title=\u017divot v extr\u00e9mech|last=|first=|date=2014|website=prirodovedci.cz|publisher=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdci|trans-title=Life in the extremes|access-date=}}</ref> reports from Antarctic expeditions,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/odlet-znacne-znesnadnilo-pocasi/296323|title=Odlet zna\u010dn\u011b znesnadnilo po\u010das\u00ed|date=2008|website=magazin.ceskenoviny.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny|trans-title=Departure made difficult due to forecast|access-date=2016-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826121145/http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/odlet-znacne-znesnadnilo-pocasi/296323|archive-date=2016-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/zprava-c-3-z-ostrova-jamese-rosse-vedecka-prace-se-rozbehla/354292|title=Zpr\u00e1va \u010d. 3 z ostrova Jamese Rosse: V\u011bdeck\u00e1 pr\u00e1ce se rozb\u011bhla|date=2009|website=magazin.ceskenoviny.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny|trans-title=Report no. 3 of the James Ross Island: Scientific work is started|access-date=2016-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826115259/http://magazin.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/zprava-c-3-z-ostrova-jamese-rosse-vedecka-prace-se-rozbehla/354292|archive-date=2016-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/leonardo/veda/_zprava/dalsi-clenove-antarkticke-expedice-jsou-na-miste--542596|title=Dal\u0161\u00ed \u010dlenov\u00e9 antarktick\u00e9 expedice jsou na m\u00edst\u011b|date=2009|website=rozhlas.cz|publisher=\u010cesk\u00fd rozhlas|trans-title=Other members of the Antarctic expedition are in place|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> and lake ecosystems at James Ross Island.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prirodovedci.cz/storage/files/184/prirodovedci-03-2015-nahled-01.pdf|title=Antarktida|last=|first=|date=2015|website=prirodovedci.cz|publisher=P\u0159\u00edrodov\u011bdci|trans-title=Antarctica|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://casopis.vesmir.cz/clanek/jezera-ostrova-jamese-rosse|title=Jezera ostrova Jamese Rosse|date=2012|website=casopis.vesmir.cz|publisher=Vesmir|trans-title=Lake James Ross Island|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abicko.avcr.cz/2013/07/06/antarktida.html|title=\u010cesk\u00e1 stopa v Antarktid\u011b|last=|first=|date=2013|website=abicko.avcr.cz|publisher=Academic bulletin|trans-title=Czech footprint in Antarctica|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honours==\nNedbalov\u00e1 was awarded the [[Czech Academy of Sciences|Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic]] Award to Young Researchers for Outstanding Achievements in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.avcr.cz/en/about-us/awards/prizes-of-the-cas/|title=Prizes of the CAS|website=www.avcr.cz|publisher=Akademie v\u011bd \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.cryoeco.eu/linda-nedbalova/ Linda Nedbalova's webpage]\n* [https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=L1CmfTAAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao Linda Nedbalova] on [[Google scholar]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nedbalova, Linda}}\n\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century biologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Czech biologists]]\n[[Category:Czech women biologists]]\n[[Category:Czech Antarctic scientists]]\n[[Category:Women Antarctic scientists]]\n[[Category:Phycologists]]\n[[Category:Women phycologists]]\n", "name_user": "Kj cheetham", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linda_Nedbalov%C3%A1"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Czechia per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by region\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Czech Republic]]\n| first_case      = Unknown\n| arrival_date    = 1 March 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days\n | month1 = 03\n | day1   = 1\n | year1  = 2020\n | month2 = \n | day2   = \n | year2  = }} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[Italy]]\n| recovery_cases  = 181<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| deaths          = 91<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 5,033<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] saw its first three confirmed cases in the [[Czech Republic]] on 1 March 2020. On 12 March, the government declared a [[state of emergency]], for the first time in the country's modern history for the area of the entire country. On 16 March, the country closed its borders, forbade the entry of foreigners and issued a nationwide curfew. While originally planned until 24 March, the measures were later extended until 1 April<ref name=\"apnews\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-republic-severely-limits-freedom-of-movement-in-order-to-slow-down-coronavirus-spread|title=Czech Republic goes into quarantine to slow down coronavirus spread|website=Radio Prague International|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> and then again until the end of State of Emergency<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /> which was extended by the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] until 30 April 2020.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.psp.cz/eknih/2017ps/stenprot/043schuz/s043037.htm#h8 |title=P\u010cR, PS 2017 , 43. sch\u016fze, \u010d\u00e1st 37 (7. 4. 2020) |publisher=Psp.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nCzech Republic started gradual easing of measures from 7 April 2020 onwards.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /><ref name=\"sports allowed\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/The Czech Republic medical cases chart}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:80%; float:right; clear:right; margin:0 0 0.5em 1em;\"\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in the Czech Republic<ref name=\":0\"/>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Date\n! colspan=\"2\" | Confirmed\n! colspan=\"2\" | Recovered\n! colspan=\"2\" | Deaths\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Active<br / >cases\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Tested<br/>(Total)\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Detected<br/>ratio\n|-\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n|-\n! 28 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 193\n| \n|-\n! 29 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 200\n| \n|-\n! 1 March\n| 3 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 211\n| {{#exp